The paper explores the performance of inverted indexing, which is a core technique in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the performance of indexing on modern hardware, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper examines the physical characteristics of the source and target media, which relates to data storage (cs.DS) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
